actions.text: The first step in being able to regulate our emotions is noticing! This requires observing ourselves. We may notice physical changes in our body (e.g., my heart is racing, my shoulders are tense, and my cheeks are getting flushed). We may also notice thoughts that don't reflect us at our best (e.g., accusations or assumptions about another person). Once we realize we are experiencing a negative emotion, we can create the space to change it. Now, let us explore some techniques to regulate our emotions:

*Just like me*

This is a simple technique. The way it works is by creating connection with the person we are feeling negative emotion towards. Even when we are not feeling connected to them in the moment, we can regulate those emotions by adding the clause "just like me" to the thoughts we are having about them. 
Here, we try to keep ourself in their shoes , to feel empathetic. This helps us manage our negative emotions by having better understanding of the situation.  Creating that connection with the others is a quick way to build empathy and regulate our emotions in a healthy way.

*Pause and Get Curious*

This technique helps us to better understand the situation and respond accordingly, which helps us to manage impulsive emotional reactions. Fo this, we take time to think rationally about a situation and then react. 
Here, we take a deep breath and ask ourself  a question about our emotions or the situation we are in. It gives us enough space and time to make a choice about how we want to respond rather than reacting with an impulsive response. It allows us to get curious about our initial reactions, feel into our emotions, and make better decisions to regulate our emotions in a healthier way.

text: हाम्रा भावनाहरू विनियमित गर्न सक्षम हुनुको पहिलो चरण ध्यान दिनु हो! यसका लागि हामीले आफैलाई नियाल्न आवश्यक छ। हामीले हाम्रो शरीरमा शारीरिक परिवर्तनहरू देख्न सक्छौं (जस्तै, मेरो मुटु दौडिरहेको छ, मेरो काँधहरू तनावग्रस्त छन्, र मेरो गालाहरू फ्लस भइरहेको छ)। हामीले हाम्रो राम्रोसँग प्रतिबिम्बित नगर्ने विचारहरू पनि देख्न सक्छौं (जस्तै, अर्को व्यक्तिको बारेमा आरोप वा अनुमानहरू)। एकचोटि हामीले महसुस गर्यौं कि हामीले नकारात्मक भावना अनुभव गरिरहेका छौं, हामी यसलाई परिवर्तन गर्न ठाउँ सिर्जना गर्न सक्छौं। अब, हामी हाम्रा भावनाहरू विनियमित गर्न केही प्रविधिहरू अन्वेषण गरौं:

*म जस्तै*

यो एक सरल प्रविधि हो। यसले काम गर्ने तरिका भनेको व्यक्तिसँग सम्बन्ध सिर्जना गर्नु हो जसलाई हामीले नकारात्मक भावना महसुस गरिरहेका छौं। यस क्षणमा हामी तिनीहरूसँग जोडिएको महसुस नगर्दा पनि, हामी तिनीहरूको बारेमा सोचिरहेका विचारहरूमा "म जस्तै" खण्ड थपेर ती भावनाहरूलाई नियमन गर्न सक्छौं। यहाँ, हामी समानुभूति महसुस गर्न, तिनीहरूको जुत्तामा आफूलाई राख्न कोसिस गर्छौं। यसले हामीलाई परिस्थितिलाई राम्रोसँग बुझेर हाम्रा नकारात्मक भावनाहरूलाई व्यवस्थापन गर्न मद्दत गर्छ। अरूसँग त्यो जडान सिर्जना गर्नु समानुभूति निर्माण गर्ने र स्वस्थ तरिकामा हाम्रा भावनाहरूलाई विनियमित गर्ने द्रुत तरिका हो। *पज गर्नुहोस् र जिज्ञासु बनाउनुहोस्* यो प्रविधिले हामीलाई परिस्थितिलाई राम्रोसँग बुझ्न र तदनुसार प्रतिक्रिया दिन मद्दत गर्छ, जसले हामीलाई आवेगपूर्ण भावनात्मक प्रतिक्रियाहरू व्यवस्थापन गर्न मद्दत गर्छ। यसका लागि, हामी परिस्थितिको बारेमा तर्कसंगत सोच्न र त्यसपछि प्रतिक्रिया गर्न समय लिन्छौं। यहाँ, हामी गहिरो सास फेर्छौं र हाम्रा भावनाहरू वा हामी परिस्थितिको बारेमा आफैलाई प्रश्न सोध्छौं। यसले हामीलाई आवेगपूर्ण प्रतिक्रियाको साथ प्रतिक्रिया गर्नुको सट्टा हामी कसरी प्रतिक्रिया दिन चाहन्छौं भन्ने छनौट गर्न पर्याप्त ठाउँ र समय दिन्छ। यसले हामीलाई हाम्रा प्रारम्भिक प्रतिक्रियाहरूको बारेमा उत्सुक हुन, हाम्रा भावनाहरूमा महसुस गर्न, र स्वस्थ तरिकामा हाम्रा भावनाहरूलाई विनियमित गर्न राम्रो निर्णयहरू गर्न अनुमति दिन्छ।

actions.text: Substance use is a topic that affects many teenagers.
Using substances is especially risky for teens because there it interferes with brain development and it can cause a lot of accidents, fights, unwanted sexual activity and possibly even overdose.
Teens are especially vulnerable to addiction because of the way the teen brain works. 🧠

People might use substances for varying reasons. They might be curious about it, or they might think it makes them look cool, or they might think that using substances will help with stress, even though there might be other ways to cope with the stress that is less harmful.
Sometimes teens also use substances because they are being pressured into using them.

Learning to say NO is beneficial. ⛔
Type *NEXT* to know about ideas to say NO.
Knowing how to say no when being pressured to use substances is an important skill.
If you are being pressured into using substances, these are some refusal strategies you can use:

1️⃣ You can try to challenge people's assumptions about substance use: for example, if someone thinks it's cool to use substances, you could tell them that you don't think it's that cool or that there are many other things that are cooler.

2️⃣ You can think about alternatives. If someone is pressuring you because they think it will help them to manage stress, you can consider suggesting something else that will help to manage the stress that won't be as harmful. For example, You could say _"I actually find running helps me to reduce stress, so I don't see why I should use alcohol"_.

3️⃣ You can think about the consequences. For example, if someone is using substances without thinking about the harm they will cause, you could consider sharing with them what the consequences might be. For example, you could say _"Drinking will cause my grades to go down, and I don't think it's worth risking my scholarship"_.

Substance abuse leading to dependence is a very difficult situation to deal with. Given that we or our friends have developed dependence on some substance, it is very important to seek help as early as possible.

actions.text: Emotions are feelings. We are capable of experiencing thousands of different emotions as people. Some emotions are pleasant, like joy, and some can be more difficult, like sadness or anger.

All of these emotions matter, and it's okay to feel any emotion, but if you notice that you are always feeling just one thing, and it's making life difficult for you, it's not a bad idea to seek some help. Emotions can sometimes serve a purpose.
For example, fear might tell us something is unsafe, and that we should be careful and look for safety.
Frustration might tell us something isn't going the way we hoped, and that we need to solve a problem or ask for help.
Sadness might mean that we are responding to something that happened, like a loss, a fight, or even a song or a movie.
Joy might tell us something is good for our well-being, and that we should do it more often or regularly.
These are all different and some are more intense than others, but they all matter.

Do you want to know about emotion regulation?

*1*. Yes
*2*. No
Regulating our emotions is something we all do every day.
💭 Think about the last time you were angry.
What did you do? There are different ways to regulate anger, and some might be more appropriate than others.
Did you shout and become aggressive? Did you pause and go for a walk? Did you break something? Did you write a letter?
These are all ways to manage a difficult emotion, but some will have better outcomes than others.
Type *NEXT* if you want to know about ways to express your emotions.
Expressing emotions can be really tricky, and it goes together with regulating them.

In some situations, it's easy to say how we feel and to not be worried about it. In other situations, it can be more difficult. Sometimes we keep our feelings bottled up, and that can cause a lot of stress.
Some ways of expressing emotions in a helpful way might include painting 🎨, keeping a journal 📒 or talking to a friend 💬 .
